Using Tomcat 3.2.1 and Apache 1.3.17, I got an error when uploading file ex.:

In general:
html page:
...
Form to send files:
<form method="POST" action="/examples/servlet/proba" ENCTYPE="multipart/form-
data">
<input type="file" size=20 name="putmemo">
<input type=submit name="submit">
</form>
...

a part of servlet:

public void doPost(HttpServletRequest request, HttpServletResponse response) 
throws ServletException, IOException {
  FileOutputStream  outputFile = new FileOutputStream("/tmp/ing");
  PrintWriter out = response.getWriter();
  response.setContentType("text/html");
  ServletInputStream stream = request.getInputStream();
  byte[] a= new byte[100];
  int ble;
  while ( (ble=stream.read(a)) != -1 ) {
    outputFile.write(a);
  }
  outputFile.close();
  stream.close();
  out.println("Done.");
}

As you can see the idea is to upload file on the server. Everything worked OK 
when i have used mod_jserv. I have installed tomcat and there is a conclusion:
-when using apjv12 - works OK
-when using apjv13 - the browser hangs, and I go a lot of 'Y' chars on the
console, that i run tomcat.

Well, would you please tell me what is wrong ?
BTW problem occurs only when i upload binary file ex.: 500kb ziped file !!!.
